This repository contains a continuous compliance and supply-chain
dashboard for the publicly-distributed KAOS open-source packages. The
dashboard is published to GitHub Pages at
https://273v.github.io/kaos-compliance/ and is regenerated on a cron
schedule documented in `docs/METHODOLOGY.md`.

The dashboard makes specific verifiable claims about the KAOS packages.
Every claim links back to a public evidence source (GitHub Actions
workflow run, PyPI metadata, sigstore Rekor log entry, or a file in
this repository). The methodology document explains how each claim is
constructed and how a third party can independently reproduce the
verification.

This dashboard is not a substitute for an independent security audit,
a SOC 2 attestation, or any other formal third-party assurance. It is
a continuous reporting mechanism designed to give compliance and
information security reviewers a fast, evidence-backed answer to the
question "can our team depend on this package today?"
